com.mygdx.game

Class LoadSave

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mygdx.game.LoadSave
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

    public class LoadSave
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.badlogic.gdx.Screen
    This class is responsible for reading information from a save file that the user is saving their game to (which includes information such as the current level the user is on, their name, and their current time. This class also creates a user interface that renders a screen and allows for the user to be able to choose from their saves which one they would like to load.

    Instance Variables

    batch Instance of SpriteBatch used to render on screen elements

    game Instance of MainGame used to manage screen changes

    name String used to store name of player in save file

    nameOfSave String used to store name of the save file to load from

    difficulty int used to store the stage the player is on from the save file

    timeSeconds int used to store the time the player has saved in the save file

    savePanelText Instance of Texture used to store image of load panel

    savePanelSprite Instance of Sprite used to create a Sprite of the load panel

    choose Instance of JFileChooser used to select the file to load from

    Version:
    4.0 07.06.2016
    Author:
    David Le

      • fileRead

        public boolean fileRead()
        This method is used to read data from the file, as well as checking if the data read from the file is in valid format to be used. The first try-catch is used for catching various IO exceptions. The first if statement is used to determine if the current line is null. If it is, the BufferedReaders are terminated and the method returns true. If not, the String name is assigned as that current line. The second if statement determines if the name variable is empty. If it is, the boolean illegalTrue is set to true. The first and second for loops are used to run through the name and the array of illegal characters. The third if statement determines if the name contains any of the illegal characters. If it does, then the boolean illegalTrue is true. The fourth if statement is used to determine if illegalTrue is true. If it is, the BufferedReaders are closed, and the method returns true. The second try-catch is used for catching number format exceptions. The fifth if statement is used to determine if the current line is null. If it is, the BufferedReaders are closed, and the method returns true. Otherwise, the int difficulty variable is assigned to the number read from the file. The sixth if statement is used to determine if the next line is null. If it is, the BufferedReaders are terminated. Otherwise, the int timeSeconds variable gets assigned to the number read from the file. The seventh if statement is used to determine if the difficulty variable is within valid range. If not, the Buffered Readers are terminated, and the method returns true. The eighth if statement is used to determine if the timeSeconds variable is a negative number. If it is, the BufferedReaders are terminated, and the method returns true.
        Returns:
        boolean true/false based on file validity

      • show

        public void show()
        The show method is an overridden method from the Screen interface. The show method is responsible for initiating variables, setting any directories for file loading, and running any methods that need to run at the beginning of execution. The first if statement is used to determine if the saves folder exists. If it does not, one is created.
        Specified by:
        show in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen

      • render

        public void render(float delta)
        The render method is an overridden method from the Screen interface. The render method loops once every frame of game execution. The first if statement is used to determine if there is anything wrong with the save file (based off of the conditions by the fileRead() method). If there is, a JOptionPane prompt dialog displays, notifying the user that there is a problem with the save file. If the fileRead() method is false, a new save is created with the information from the file, and the screen is set to a new GameScreen with all the information read from the load file.
        Specified by:
        render in interface com.badlogic.gdx.Screen
